commit.message:
fix: replace unsafe six.PY3 with PY2 for better future compatibility with Python 4 (#10081)

* fix: fix for Python 4: replace unsafe six.PY3 with PY2

* Fix wording

fix(logging): update test assertion and core version pins (#10087)

* Adjust request params assertion in test (timeout)

* Update version pins for core dependencies

Version bumps are needed, as timeouts were introduced to API core.

* Adjust assertion in system test

An empty zone label that was missing is added.
fix(logging): deprecate resource name helper methods (via synth) (#9837)
chore(logging): change spacing in docs templates (via synth)  (#9756)
docs: add python 2 sunset banner to documentation (#9036)
chore(logging): add trailing commas (via synth) (#9560)
chore(logging): release 1.14.0 (#9471)
chore: pin 'google-cloud-core >= 1.0.3, < 2.0.0dev' (#9445)
fix(logging): fix proto copy (#9420)
chore(logging): release logging 1.13.0 (#9269)
codegen(logging): add deprecated 'start_time' / 'end_time' fields to 'LogSink'  (#9311)
docs: fix intersphinx reference to requests (#9294)
Logging: Add LoggingV2Servicer, LogSinks, logging_metrics, and log_entry. Add LogSeverity and HttpRequest types (via synth). (#9262)
ContainerEngineHandler: don't swallow stream (#9166)
Add client_options to logging v1 (#9046)
Docs: Remove CI for gh-pages, use googleapis.dev for api_core refs. (#9085)
Remove compatability badges from READMEs. (#9035)

Delete custom synth removing gRPC send/recv msg size limits. (#8939)

Now handled via gapic-generator.

Closes #8931.
